texts.value: Necessary for efficient RNA polymerase II transcription elongation past template-encoded arresting sites. The arresting sites in DNA have the property of trapping a certain fraction of elongating RNA polymerases that pass through, resulting in locked ternary complexes. Cleavage of the nascent transcript by S-II allows the resumption of elongation from the new 3'-terminus
Interacts with the basal transcription factor GTF2B. Interacts with REXO1
It is uncertain whether Met-1 or Met-2 is the initiator

features.description: Glycyl lysine isopeptide (Lys-Gly) (interchain with G-Cter in ubiquitin)
